  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Globals like `artifacts` are not available to modules required from a migration.\r\n\r\n```\r\n// migrations/02_a_migration.js\r\nconst Greeter = artifacts.require('Greeter'); // ok\r\nrequire('./my-module'); // ./my-module won't have access to artifacts global\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis issue does not happen in tests.\r\n\r\n@gnidan suggested this may be due to migrations using `@truffle/require`, which tests don't use.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/frangio/truffle-globals-repro\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit clone https://github.com/frangio/truffle-globals-repro.git\r\ncd truffle-globals-repro\r\nnpm ci\r\nnpx truffle test\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nGlobals should be global for all modules.",
